This template summarizes information about a piece of [[legislation]] or a [[:en:Bill (law)|bill]]. It is designed to be generic so that it can be used for the bills, [[:en:Statute|Statute]]s and subsidiary legislation ([[delegated legislation]]) of any [[:en:Jurisdiction|Jurisdiction]]. If you have suggestions as to how the template may be improved, please leave a message on the [[Template talk:Infobox legislation|talk page]].
Specific infoboxes for European Union, United Kingdom (national and devolved) and United States (federal only) legislation are at {{tl|Infobox EU legislation}}, {{tl|Infobox UK legislation}} and {{tl|Infobox U.S. legislation}} respectively (although this template also supports the latter two to a limited extent).
===Legislation enacted by a legislature (e.g. an Act of Parliament/Congress)=== See next section for bills that did not pass or is still being considered by the legislature. {{Hidden begin|title=Click [show] to view}} <syntaxhighlight lang="wikitext" style="overflow:auto"> {{Infobox legislation |short_title = |legislature = <!-- Name of enacting legislature, wikilinked. --> |image = |imagesize = |image_upright = |imagealt = |caption = |long_title = |citation = |territorial_extent = |enacted_by = <!-- For bicameral legislatures, this is the chamber the bill was first introduced. --> |date_enacted = <!-- Pick one of date_enacted or date_passed as appropriate in jurisdiction. --> |date_passed = <!-- Pick one of date_enacted or date_passed as appropriate in jurisdiction. --> |enacted_by2 = <!-- For bicameral legislatures only. Use if bill passed the second chamber. --> |date_enacted2 = <!-- For bicameral legislatures only. Pick one of date_enacted2 or date_passed2 as appropriate in jurisdiction. --> |date_passed2 = <!-- For bicameral legislatures only. Pick one of date_enacted2 or date_passed2 as appropriate in jurisdiction. --> |date_assented = <!-- Pick none or one of date_assented, royal_assent or date_signed as appropriate in jurisdiction. --> |assented_by = <!-- Only use if date_assented or royal_assent is used. --> |royal_assent = <!-- Pick none or one of date_assented, royal_assent or date_signed as appropriate in jurisdiction. --> |date_signed = <!-- Pick none or one of date_assented, royal_assent or date_signed as appropriate in jurisdiction. --> |signed_by = <!-- Only use if date_signed is used. --> <!-- Use date_vetoed, vetoed_by, veto_type, veto_overridden, and reference_holding if bill was vetoed but the veto was overridden, or, for constitutional vetoes, the constitutional court held that the bill is constitutional. --> |date_vetoed = <!-- For jurisdiction where a veto is used. --> |vetoed_by = <!-- Only use if date_vetoed is used. --> |veto_type = <!-- Only use if the jurisdiction allows for several types of veto, e.g. returning a bill to the legislature or referring it to a constitutional court. Pocket vetoes should not be placed here. --> |veto_overridden = <!-- Date on which the veto was overridden. Pocket vetoes and constitutional vetoes should not be placed here; however, if the veto results in a referendum on the bill, the date of that referendum should be here, with a wiki link where possible. --> |reference_holding = <!-- For jurisdictions where a constitutional veto (a bill is referred to the supreme or constitutional court) is used. The holding of the court as to the constitutionality of a bill; wikilink or external link to the ruling where possible. --> |date_became_law_by_inaction = <!-- For jurisdiction where a pocket approval is used (e.g. if no action is taken on a bill after it is presented to the head of state, it becomes law automatically). --> |date_commenced = <!-- Pick one of date_commenced or date_effective as appropriate in jurisdiction. --> |date_effective = <!-- Pick one of date_commenced or date_effective as appropriate in jurisdiction. --> |date_of_expiry = |date_repealed = |administered_by = |bill_history_url = |bill = <!-- Name of relevant bill debated in the chamber listed in enacted_by or considered_by. Omit if the legislation is still a bill in this chamber and the bill name used in short_title. --> |bill_citation = |bill_date = |introduced_by = <!-- Name of member introducing the bill in the chamber. --> |committee_responsible = <!-- Name of committee of the chamber responsible for the bill, in short form (e.g. "Ways and Means", not "House Committee on Ways and Means"). --> |preliminary_reading = |preliminary_reading_for = |preliminary_reading_against = |preliminary_reading_abstention = |preliminary_reading_absent = |preliminary_reading_presentnotvoting = |1st_reading = |1st_reading_for = |1st_reading_against = |1st_reading_abstention = |1st_reading_absent = |1st_reading_presentnotvoting = |committee_post1st = <!-- If consideration by committee occurs between 1st and 2nd readings; pick none or one of committee_post1st or committee_post2nd as appropriate in jurisdiction. --> |2nd_reading = |2nd_reading_for = |2nd_reading_against = |2nd_reading_abstention = |2nd_reading_absent = |2nd_reading_presentnotvoting = |committee_post2nd = <!-- If consideration by committee occurs between 2nd and 3rd readings; pick none or one of committee_post1st or committee_post2nd as appropriate in jurisdiction. --> |committee_whole_label = |committee_whole = |3rd_reading = |3rd_reading_for = |3rd_reading_against = |3rd_reading_abstention = |3rd_reading_absent = |3rd_reading_presentnotvoting = |passed = <!-- For jurisdictions without numbered readings only. --> |passed_for = <!-- For jurisdictions without numbered readings only. --> |passed_against = <!-- For jurisdictions without numbered readings only. --> |passed_abstention = <!-- For jurisdictions without numbered readings only. --> |passed_absent = <!-- For jurisdictions without numbered readings only. --> |passed_presentnotvoting = <!-- For jurisdictions without numbered readings only. --> |conf_committee_passed = <!-- For bicameral legislatures only. --> |conf_committee_passed_for = <!-- For bicameral legislatures only. --> |conf_committee_passed_against = <!-- For bicameral legislatures only. --> |conf_committee_passed_abstention = <!-- For bicameral legislatures only. --> |conf_committee_passed_absent = <!-- For bicameral legislatures only. --> |conf_committee_passed_presentnotvoting = <!-- For bicameral legislatures only. --> |committee_report = |bill2 = <!-- For bicameral legislatures only. Name of relevant bill debated in the chamber listed in enacted_by2 or considered_by2. --> |bill_citation2 = <!-- For bicameral legislatures only. --> |bill_date2 = <!-- For bicameral legislatures only. --> |introduced_by2 = <!-- For bicameral legislatures only. Name of member introducing the bill in the chamber. --> |committee_responsible2 = <!-- For bicameral legislatures only. Name of committee of the chamber responsible for the bill, in short form (e.g. "Ways and Means", not "House Committee on Ways and Means"). --> |preliminary_reading2 = <!-- For bicameral legislatures only. --> |preliminary_reading2_for = <!-- For bicameral legislatures only. --> |preliminary_reading2_against = <!-- For bicameral legislatures only. --> |preliminary_reading2_abstention = <!-- For bicameral legislatures only. --> |preliminary_reading2_absent = <!-- For bicameral legislatures only. --> |preliminary_reading2_presentnotvoting = <!-- For bicameral legislatures only. --> |1st_reading2 = <!-- For bicameral legislatures only. --> |1st_reading2 = <!-- For bicameral legislatures only. --> |1st_reading2_for = <!-- For bicameral legislatures only. --> |1st_reading2_against = <!-- For bicameral legislatures only. --> |1st_reading2_abstention = <!-- For bicameral legislatures only. --> |1st_reading2_absent = <!-- For bicameral legislatures only. --> |1st_reading2_presentnotvoting = <!-- For bicameral legislatures only. --> |committee_post1st2 = <!-- For bicameral legislatures only. If consideration by committee occurs between 1st and 2nd readings; pick none or one of committee_post1st or committee_post2nd as appropriate in jurisdiction. --> |2nd_reading2 = <!-- For bicameral legislatures only. Specify date range for multi-day readings. --> |2nd_reading2 = <!-- For bicameral legislatures only. --> |2nd_reading2_for = <!-- For bicameral legislatures only. --> |2nd_reading2_against = <!-- For bicameral legislatures only. --> |2nd_reading2_abstention = <!-- For bicameral legislatures only. --> |2nd_reading2_absent = <!-- For bicameral legislatures only. --> |2nd_reading2_presentnotvoting = <!-- For bicameral legislatures only. --> |committee_post2nd2 = <!-- For bicameral legislatures only. If consideration by committee occurs between 2nd and 3rd readings; pick none or one of committee_post1st or committee_post2