This template summarizes information about a piece of [[legislation]] or a [[:en:Bill (law)|bill]]. It is designed to be generic so that it can be used for the bills, [[:en:Statute|Statute]]s and subsidiary legislation ([[delegated legislation]]) of any [[:en:Jurisdiction|Jurisdiction]]. If you have suggestions as to how the template may be improved, please leave a message on the [[Template talk:Infobox legislation|talk page]].
Specific infoboxes for European Union, United Kingdom (national and devolved) and United States (federal only) legislation are at {{tl|Infobox EU legislation}}, {{tl|Infobox UK legislation}} and {{tl|Infobox U.S. legislation}} respectively (although this template also supports the latter two to a limited extent).
===Legislation enacted by a legislature (e.g. an Act of Parliament/Congress)=== See next section for bills that did not pass or is still being considered by the legislature. {{Hidden begin|title=Click [show] to view}} <syntaxhighlight lang="wikitext" style="overflow:auto"> {{Infobox legislation |short_title = |legislature = |image = |imagesize = |image_upright = |imagealt = |caption = |long_title = |citation = |territorial_extent = |enacted_by = |date_enacted = |date_passed = |enacted_by2 = |date_enacted2 = |date_passed2 = |date_assented = |assented_by = |royal_assent = |date_signed = |signed_by =
